net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator

Class NSGA2ConstrainedComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.MOSolutionComparator
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.ConstrainedComparator
        • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.NSGA2ConstrainedComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<net.sf.jclec.IIndividual>

    public class NSGA2ConstrainedComparator
extends ConstrainedComparator
    Compare two individuals in a problem with constraints as proposed in NSGA-II. This comparator establishes that two infeasible individuals should be compared using the degree of constraint violation.

    Paper: K. Deb, A. Pratap, S. Agarwal, and T. Meyarivan, “A fast and elitist multiobjective genetic algorithm: NSGA-II,” IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation, vol. 6, no. 2, pp. 182–197, 2002.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare(net.sf.jclec.IIndividual arg0,
                   net.sf.jclec.IIndividual arg1)
        Compare two individuals. The following comparisons are made:
        • If one individual is feasible and the other is infeasible, the first is preferred.
        • If both individuals are infeasible, the one with the lowest degree of constraint violation is preferred.
        • If both individuals are feasible, compare them by fitness.
